Elbow method - K-Means¶

In [ ]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

# Inicializar dicionários para armazenar as features e os dados de cada dataset
features = {}
X = {}
for i in range(1, 5):
    features[i] = dataset[i].columns
    X[i] = dataset[i][features[i]].values  # Converter para array

# plotar o método do cotovelo de cada dataset
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=4, ncols=1, figsize=(8, 16))

# Calcular e plotar o método do cotovelo pra cada dataset
for i in range(1, 5):
    distortions = []
    silhouette_scores = []
    for k in range(1, 20):
        km = KMeans(n_clusters=k, init='k-means++', n_init=30, max_iter=500, random_state=0)
        km.fit(X[i])
        distortions.append(km.inertia_)
        if k > 1:
            silhouette_scores.append(silhouette_score(X[i], km.labels_))
        else:
            silhouette_scores.append(0)

    # Plotar
    axes[i-1].plot(range(1, 20), distortions, marker='o')
    axes[i-1].set_xlabel('Number of clusters')
    axes[i-1].set_ylabel('Distortion')
    axes[i-1].set_title(f'Método do Cotovelo - Dataset {i}')
    axes[i-1].grid(True)

    # Exibir distorções
    print(f"\nDataset{i}:")
    for k in range(len(distortions)):
        print(f"k={k+1}: Inertia={distortions[k]:.2f}, Silhouette={silhouette_scores[k]:.3f}")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Plotando clusters e seus centróides com K-Means¶

In [ ]:
colors = ['lightblue', 'red', 'green', 'purple', 'orange', 'pink', 'lightgreen', 'darkblue', 'yellow', 'cyan', 'magenta', 'lime', 'teal', 'brown', 'gray', 'indigo']
markers = ['o', 's', '^', 'v', '*', 'D', 'd', 'p', 'h', 'H']

# Dataset 1:

km = KMeans(n_clusters=2,
            init='k-means++',
            n_init=30,
            max_iter=500,
            tol=1e-04,
            random_state=0)

y_km = km.fit_predict(X[1])
plt.scatter(X[1][y_km == 0, 0],
            X[1][y_km == 0, 1],
            s=50, c='lightgreen',
            marker='o', edgecolor='white',
            label='Cluster 1')
plt.scatter(X[1][y_km == 1, 0],
            X[1][y_km == 1, 1],
            s=50, c='orange',
            marker='o', edgecolor='white',
            label='Cluster 2')
plt.scatter(km.cluster_centers_[:, 0],
            km.cluster_centers_[:, 1],
            s=250, marker='*',
            c='red', edgecolor='black',
            label='Centroids')

plt.xlabel('Feature 1')
plt.ylabel('Feature 2')
plt.title(f'K-Means - Dataset 1')

plt.legend(scatterpoints=1)
plt.grid()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

                edgecolor='black', label=f'Cluster {label + 1}')

# Plotar centróides
ax4.scatter(km.cluster_centers_[:, 0], km.cluster_centers_[:, 1],
            s=250, marker='*', c='red', edgecolor='black',
            label='Centroids')

ax4.set_xlabel('Feature 1')
ax4.set_ylabel('Feature 2')
ax4.set_title(f'K-Means - Dataset 4')
ax4.legend()
ax4.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

DBSCAN¶

from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN

# Dataset 1
db1 = DBSCAN(eps=0.9, min_samples=5, metric='euclidean')
y_db1 = db1.fit_predict(X[1])  # Predizer clusters pra dataset 1

# Identificar clusters e ruído
unique_labels1 = np.unique(y_db1)
n_clusters1 = len(unique_labels1) - (-1 in unique_labels1)  # Exclui ruído (-1)
n_noise1 = list(y_db1).count(-1)

# Plotar scatter plot para Dataset 1
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
colors = ['lightblue', 'red', 'green', 'purple', 'orange', 'pink', 'lightgreen', 'darkblue', 'yellow', 'cyan', 'magenta', 'lime', 'teal', 'brown', 'gray', 'indigo']
markers = ['o', 's', '^', 'v', '*', 'o', 's', '^', 'v', '*', 'o', 's', '^', 'v', '*',]
for label in unique_labels1:
    if label == -1:  # Ruído
        ax1.scatter(X[1][y_db1 == label, 0], X[1][y_db1 == label, 1],
                   c='black', marker='x', s=20,
                   label='Ruído' if label == -1 else f'Cluster {label + 1}')
    else:  # Clusters
        ax1.scatter(X[1][y_db1 == label, 0], X[1][y_db1 == label, 1],
                   c=colors[label % len(colors)], marker=markers[label % len(markers)], s=40,
                   edgecolor='black', label=f'Cluster {label + 1}')
ax1.set_xlabel('Feature 1')
ax1.set_ylabel('Feature 2')
ax1.set_title(f'DBSCAN - Dataset 1 (Clusters: {n_clusters1}, Ruído: {n_noise1})')
ax1.legend()
ax1.grid(True)

# Imprimir estatísticas para Dataset 1
print(f"\nDataset 1:")
print(f"Número de clusters: {n_clusters1}")
print(f"Número de pontos classificados como ruído: {n_noise1}")
